# Objective
This test ensures the validator correctly identifies and reports a calendar date that is not before a specified time, enforcing the validation constraint.

# Preconditions
1. The test environment is properly set up with all necessary tools and classes, including validator, validator builder, calendar entry local date-time, and local date-time.
2. The current time (local date-time now) is set to be 10 hours after the specified time.
3. A calendar entry local date-time object is created using the current time.

# Expected Results
1. The validation process fails, indicating the calendar date is invalid.
2. Exactly one error is reported due to the validation failure.
3. The error message states that the date must be before the specified time, formatted as "datetime" has to be before " + now.minusHours(10).
